===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*(s)mey-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|smilen|t=to smile}}, from {{der|en|non|smíla|t=to smile}} (compare {{cog|da|smile}}, {{cog|sv|smila||to smile}}), from {{der|en|gem-pro|*smīlijaną}}, {{m|gem-pro|*smirōną|t=to smile}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*smey-|t=to laugh, be glad, wonder}}. Cognate with {{cog|stq|smielje|t=to smile}}, {{cog|nds|smielen|t=to smile}}, {{cog|nl|smuilen|t=to smile}}, {{cog|gmh|smielen|t=to smile}}. Related also to {{cog|goh|smierōn|t=to smile}}, {{cog|ang|smerian|t=to laugh at}}, {{cog|ang|smercian}}, {{m|ang|smearcian}} {{gloss|"to smile"; > {{cog|en|smirk}}}}, {{cog|la|miror|t=to wonder at}}.

